ommon in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":15,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":28,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":37,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert FitzNeale was born in 1300, in Buckinghamshire, England, his father, John FitzNeale, was 50 and his mother, Blanche Roche, was 38. He married Mrs Robert FitzNeale before 1352, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1351."},"et":{"1300–after 1351":"1300–pärast 1351","1300–1351":"1300–1351","–Female":"Surnud","1352–1373":"1352–1373","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1262–1315":"1262–1315","before 1300":"enne 1300","before 1352":"enne 1352","1352":"1352","1373":"1373","1351":"1351","1262":"1262","1250":"1250","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","after 1351":"pärast 1351","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1300–after 1351":"1300–1351 jälkeen","1300–1351":"1300–1351","–Female":"Kuollut","1352–1373":"1352–1373","1250–Male"